## Big O Notation
Big O describes how runtime or space requirements grow as the input size `n` grows.
```python
def print_all(items):
    for i in items: print(i)  # O(n) Time, O(1) Space

def print_pairs(items):
    for i in items:
        for j in items: print(i, j)  # O(n^2) Time
```

